&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;NEONATAL UNIT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Neonatal Staff Nurses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full / Part Time Permanent Posts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cross site working at Birmingham Heartlands and Good Hope as part of University Hospitals Birmingham&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Heartlands and Good Hope Hospitals as part of University Birmingham provides Neonatal care to support over 10,000 deliveries at 3 hospitals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Heartlands, is a Level 3 neonatal unit &amp; Good Hope provides care for babies over 34 weeks gestation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;All posts are rotational to provide the service across the Good Hope and Heartlands Hospitals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Heartlands, is a busy Level 3 unit consisting of 32 cots comprising of 6 ITU, 6 HDU &amp; 20 Special Care with approximately 700 admissions each year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a great team spirit with all staff working closely together.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer a wide variety of experiences in all areas of neonatal care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Vibrant Intensive Care where skills can be gained in conventional ventilation and alternative therapies such as High Frequency Oscillation &amp; Nitric Oxide, whilst continuing with Non-invasive ventilation with CPAP &amp; Biphasic CPAP and HHF.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our ITU nurses are encouraged to continue to develop within their role to include cannulation &amp; blood gas analysis, available through our team of ANNP’S.  There also regular simulation sessions and learning opportunities including numerous FREE study days that are provided by our neonatal network (SWMNN).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We work closely with Good Hope Hospital to provide a support service for those babies that are nearing discharge, including provision of family support via our expanding Neonatal Community Outreach team and Transitional Care unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Innovative and progressive, we are always looking to improve the care we give through research &amp; networking.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Professional development is both encouraged &amp; supported here with a core induction programme, Intravenous therapy course, Neonatal Life Support and preceptorship programmes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to delivering high quality family centred care with champions in Family Integrated Care and Breastfeeding support to ensure an integrated and supportive approach to the care we deliver, with the baby and their family being at the forefront of everything we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A comprehensive corporate and Neonatal induction is provided along with a dedicated mentor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Yearly appraisals against a Professional Portfolio are performed in line with KSF requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We need motivated, enthusiastic Band 5 nurses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; ENB 405/ BSC Clinical Nursing Studies - Critical Care Pathway desirable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experienced or newly qualified Child Branch, Midwives or Adult Branch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Opportunity to complete the BSC Clinical Nursing Studies - Critical Care Pathway in the future&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;                           For further information or an informal visit please contact below&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Laura Hammond Senior Ward Sister ITU/HDU Neonatal Unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tel: 0121 424 2720/47904 or Email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;laura.hammond@heartofengland.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; OR Katy Pettit Neonatal Community Outreach Team and Transitional Care Lead Nurse on Tel: 0121 424 2722 Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;katy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;pettit@heartofengland.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date 9th November 2020&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held on 20th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;At University Hospitals Birmingham we support flexible working and welcome applications from nurses seeking flexible working opportunities and family friendly working hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
